body:
### Motivation

Configuring a Consumer vs consuming are two orthogonal concerns. By including a MessageListener in the ConsumerConfiguration object we are conflating these two issues. I propose deprecating the set/getListener methods from the ConsumerConfiguration and the ReaderConfiguration and instead allow them to become specified on subscribe.

### Modifications

I have deprecated the set/getListener methods on the ReaderConfiguration and the ConsumerConfiguration objects and added Consumer and Reader factory methods to the PulsarClient which allow a Listener to be specified directly when called. A user can still set a listener on the configuration object but if one of the new methods are called it will be ignored in favor of the one given. An alternative would be to call both.

With Java8+ the following, more natural usage, is possible:

```
client.subscribe("topic", "subscription", (consumer, message) -> {
    // DO SOMETHING WITH MESSAGE
});
```
